
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes

class GasStation {
    - id: String (unique)
    - address: String
}

class FuelPump {
    - number: Integer
    - isSelfService: Boolean
}

class Fuel {
    - name: String (unique)
    - octaneRating: Double
}

class DailyPrice {
    - date: Date
    - pricePerLiter: Double
}

class FuelPurchase {
    - id: String (unique)
    - litersDispensed: Double
}

' Associations and relationships

GasStation "1" *-- "0..12" FuelPump : has
FuelPump "1" --> "1..*" Fuel : offers
GasStation "1" --> "0..*" DailyPrice : archives
DailyPrice "1" --> "1" Fuel : for
DailyPrice "1" --> "1" GasStation : at
FuelPurchase "1" --> "1" FuelPump : at
FuelPurchase "1" --> "1" Fuel : of
FuelPurchase "1" --> "1" DailyPrice : with
FuelPurchase "1" --> "1" GasStation : in

@enduml

---

### Explanation:

- **GasStation**: Represents a single gas station with a unique ID and address.
- **FuelPump**: Each pump has a number and is marked as self-service or not. A gas station can have up to 12 fuel pumps.
- **Fuel**: Describes the type of fuel by name and octane rating.
- **DailyPrice**: Tracks the price per liter of a specific fuel at a specific gas station on a specific date.
- **FuelPurchase**: Records a purchase including which fuel was bought at which pump, using which daily price, and how many liters were dispensed.

